                            <p class="text-justify">The nightvision capability of your INSTAR Camera utilizes infrared light with a wavelength of 850nm. Diodes in this wavelength range still emit some light in the visible range (red) which is the cause of the red gleam that you can see when looking directly into the infrared LEDs. Only the spotlight IN-905 (940) uses LEDs that are completely invisible to the human eye!</p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-12 mb">
