                            <p class="text-justify">The application of invisible 940nm diodes comes with the disadvantage of effectively halving the operating range of your spotlight! The cause for this effect is the decreased sensitivity of the imaging sensor, which is falling rapidly with the increasing wavelength in the IR region. Furthermore, there is an increase in the air’s opacity for light in the range around 900nm. The application of a 940nm spotlight is only recommended, <strong>if an invisible illumination of the observed area is deemed necessary</strong>.</p>
                        </div>

